General Summary:
 Job Overview: (Computer Vision/ML Engineer)
We are searching for a computer vision/ML engineer to be part of the Qualcomm AI Processor systems team responsible for developing video processing, computer vision and machine learning based applications and use cases developed for Qualcomm Snapdragon processors. The candidate will work on new cutting-edge algorithms in the areas of computer vision, image/video processing and machine learning, and contribute to research and development of new applications for mobile and edge devices. The responsibilities include reviewing and understanding the latest developments in the field of video processing and computer vision as well as artificial intelligence, developing new video processing and computer vision algorithms that run on Qualcomm Snapdragon processors in real time at low power, leveraging the latest developments in the field of artificial intelligence to develop low power, efficient solutions for mobile applications and work closely with the hardware and software teams and support implementation and commercialization of our algorithms on Qualcomm Snapdragon devices.
Minimum Qualifications:
Bachelor or master’s degree in electrical or computer engineering or related fields;
Solid understanding of video processing and computer vision algorithms;
Solid understanding of machine learning algorithms;
Excellent programming skills in Python, C/C++, Linux and Windows;
Experience with machine learning frameworks like TensorFlow, PyTorch;
Strong motivation and capabilities in learning new subjects especially in the field of video processing, computer vision and artificial intelligence;
Strong problem-solving skills;
Effective interpersonal communications skill (written and verbal);
Analytical, thorough, resourceful and detail-oriented;
Self-motivated, hardworking, and flexible.
